cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.GT, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with maximizing degrees of freedom in a wireless network under a backhaul load constraint, which is a classic problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the design of backhaul networks and their impact on the performance of cellular downlink networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper considers a linear interference channel model where each transmitter is connected to a receiver having the same index as well as one succeeding receiver, which can be seen as a social network or information network. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the optimal assignment of messages to transmitters, which can be viewed as a game-theoretic problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions zero-forcing transmit beamforming, which is a technique used in multimedia communication systems.
